Format:
Date, Ver (Full Release, Major Feature, Feature Tweaks / Bug Fixes)
Commit Message
- Detailed points of changes

November 10th, 2025, Ver 1.0.0
Initial commit: RSL Parser and Types
- Added Types for Rituals (the entire script), Commands (either an Action or Conditional), Conditionals (an if, else statement with Commands inside it), and Actions (the most fundamental operations)
- Added a parser to build the Ritual tree. Rituals can now be read through and printed as a tree through the printTree function
- Created RSLang.md documentation for the Ritual Scripting Language
- Added example RSL files (example.RSL and example2.RSL)

November 11th, 2025, Ver 1.1.0
Added base framework for performing rituals
- Added simple framework for the execution order of performing rituals
- Implemented performRitual function to execute rituals on file objects

November 11th, 2025, Ver 1.1.1
Added execution for actions and evaluation of conditions
- Implemented the move, copy and delete actions
- Implemented the exists, name has, path has, type has, file has, name ==, type ==, size ==, size <, size >, size ==, age <, age >, age ==, is_dir, and is_file conditions
- Added CHANGELOG file to track project history

November 13th, 2025, Ver 1.1.2
Fixed forward declaration mismatch
- Fixed function signature mismatches in Executor.h
- Resolved compilation errors with forward declarations

November 13th, 2025, Ver 1.2.0
Reorganized files and functions and created CMake files for building
- Created CMakeLists.txt for project build configuration
- Added build.sh script for convenient building
- Created BUILD.md documentation for build instructions
- Moved CHANGELOG to docs/ directory
- Converted Parser.cpp to Parser.h (header-only implementation)
- Added Helpers.h with utility functions (trim function)
- Moved example RSL files to tests/ directory
- Integrated efsw library for file system watching

November 13th, 2025, Ver 1.3.0
Added a Manager to start all rituals and a Watcher to observe file changes and trigger rituals
- Implemented Manager.h to coordinate ritual execution
- Implemented Watcher.h with efsw integration for file system monitoring
- Added Scheduler.h framework for time-based ritual triggers
- Expanded Helpers.h with file extension and directory extraction utilities
- Moved helper functions from Types.h to Helpers.h for better organization
- Added support for watching directories and triggering rituals on file events

November 20th, 2025, Ver 1.3.1
Fixed file watcher implementation and action execution
- Fixed Watcher object lifetime issue - changed beginWatching to return pointer to keep watcher alive
- Implemented tilde (~) path expansion in executeAction for home directory support
- Enhanced move and copy actions to properly handle directory destinations
- Added automatic filename appending when destination is a directory
- Added comprehensive debug logging to track file events and action execution
- Added error handling with try-catch for filesystem operations
- Created desktop_watcher.RSL test file for Desktop to Downloads file movement
- Updated main.cpp to properly manage watcher lifetime and prevent premature destruction
- Added header guards to Helpers.h to prevent multiple definition errors
- Successfully tested end-to-end file watching and automatic file movement

November 20th, 2025, Ver 1.3.2
Enhanced delete action and condition evaluation
- Changed delete action to move files to Trash (~/.Trash) instead of permanent deletion
- Added erase action for permanent file deletion when needed
- Implemented automatic timestamp appending for duplicate filenames in Trash
- Fixed type comparison in evaluate() to properly strip quotes from condition values
- Added comprehensive debug logging to condition evaluation
- Added chrono header for timestamp generation
- Verified conditional file deletion based on file type
